  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "De 25:1-19. Stripes Must Not Exceed Forty.Judges must do justly,  Deu 25:1,2. Stripes not to exceed forty,  Deu 25:3. The threshing ox not to be muzzled,  Deu 25:4. The duty of raising seed unto a brother,  Deu 25:5-10. The punishment of an immodest woman,  Deu 25:11,12. A just weight and measure,  Deu 25:13-16. The memory of Amalek is to be blotted out,  Deu 25:17-19.  A controversy about criminal matters, as it follows. They shall justify, i.e. acquit him from guilt and false accusations, and free him from punishment. Condemn the wicked;  declare him guilty, and pass sentence of condemnation to suitable punishments upon him. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "De 25:1-19. Stripes Must Not Exceed Forty.Judges must do justly, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:1,2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Stripes not to exceed forty, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The threshing ox not to be muzzled, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The duty of raising seed unto a brother, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:5-10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The punishment of an immodest woman, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:11,12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". A just weight and measure, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:13-16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The memory of Amalek is to be blotted out, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bldvs",
            "text": " Deu 25:17-19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "A controversy",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " about criminal matters, as it follows. They shall justify, i.e. acquit him from guilt and false accusations, and free him from punishment. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Condemn the wicked; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " declare him guilty, and pass sentence of condemnation to suitable punishments upon him. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
